Onee-chan are called 'compatible individuals' in

I examined the locker and discovered a hidden
staircase!!
Pink Snake Gang.

It is a mutant crime organization that nests in
this city.

They appear and disappear without a trace, never
letting their tail be caught. They possess a high
level of technical skill that is unexpected for a
criminal organization.

The only thing that has barely been identified are
the code names of the three executives.

Red, Blue, and Purple. It is rumored that all of
them are powerful mutants...

On the contrary, if we capture these three
executives, the Pink Snake Gang will be destroyed.

We will continue our investigation with the top
priority of finding the location of the
executives, and this time we have decided to
investigate this abandoned house.

Of course, there was also the possibility that
this was false information...
\C[18]Sakura\C[0]: I see, that's a hit.
\C[23]Rurika\C[0]: Yes, it seems to be a hit.

forward!
Mutant Soldier: Pew! Pew! Pew!

These guys are mutant soldiers. They are members
of the Pink Snake Gang, who are produced using
illegal technology.

These soldiers, created using biotechnology and
electronic engineering, may not use language, but
they have high intelligence and can be considered
the field commanders of the Pink Snake Gang...
That's right.

In a way, they are disposable, but that's exactly
why no matter how many we capture, it won't lead
to the organization. Rurika Onee-san said they are
troublesome opponents.

Their combat abilities are high, and it is the
limit for a few people to face them with regular
police equipment... Sakura Onee-san said that.

Anyway, they're a vicious group that's disturbing
the peace of the city by using soldiers illegally
multiplied with high technological power...
